| Kazakhstan
| align=right | {{ntsh|76000}}[[+7 6]], [[+7 7]]&lt;ref name=&quot;zone7&quot;&gt;Russia, Kazakhstan, and Abkhazia make up the Seventh World Numbering Zone. From August 2007, Kazakhstan changed all area codes to start with 7; however, 6 is also reserved for Kazakhstan. Digits 3, 4, and 5 are reserved for Russia. Abkhazia was assigned +7&amp;nbsp;840 for landline and +7&amp;nbsp;940 for mobile operators on 28 September 2009. Abkhazia will also continue using +995&amp;nbsp;44. Other digits are reserved for Russia. Currently, there are no internationally accessible numbers starting with 0, 1, 2 or 5 – these are access codes and similar arrangements.&lt;/ref&gt;
